The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 07 September is 3,058 (353.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 03 September, there were 78 new confirmed cases (9.0 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 27 August, there were 45 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 73% (33 extra cases).
